on stern-wheel tinclad [[Minesweeper (ship)|minesweeper]] and gunboat sunk by a naval mine (called a "torpedo" at the time) in [[Mobile Bay]]. | |- |[[USS Tecumseh (1863)|USS ''Tecumseh'']] |5 August 1864 |A Union [[Monitor (warship)|monitor warship]] sunk by a naval mine (called a "torpedo" at the time) during the [[Battle of Mobile Bay]].<ref name="civwarshipwrecks"/> |{{coord|30|13|54|N|88|1|33|W|name=USS Tecumseh (1863)}} |- |[[CSS Tuscaloosa (ironclad)|CSS ''Tuscaloosa'']] |12 April 1865 |A [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] [[ironclad warship]] scuttled in [[Spanish River (Alabama)|Spanish River]] to avoid capture. |{{coord|30.76924|-88.02053|name=CSS Tuscaloosa (ironclad)}} |}
