ire Island]]. | |- |[[MV Gwendoline Steers|MV ''Gwendoline Steers'']] |30 December 1962 |A [[tugboat]] that sunk on the approach to [[Huntington Bay, New York|Huntington Bay]]. | |- |''[[Guggenheim Treasure|Harold]]'' |26 September 1903 |The barge moved out of dock at the [[South Street Seaport]] in New York City with 7,700 silver and lead ingots, bound for [[American Smelting and Refining Company]] in [[Perth Amboy, New Jersey]]. The silver and the smelters belonged to the Guggenheim family. The barge sank, and was never recovered. | |- |''[[Holland III]]'' |November 1883 |A prototype [[submarine]] built by [[John Philip Holland]] and stolen by the [[Fenian Brotherhood]], who accidentally sunk it off [[Whitestone, Queens|Whitestone]]. | |- |[[HMS Hussar (1763)|HMS ''Hussar'']] |23 November 1780 |A [[frigate]] that sank near [[Long Island Sound]]. | |- |[[USRC Jefferson (1832)|USRC ''Jefferson'']] |15 December 1847 |A [[cutter (boat)|cutter]] wrecked off [[Gardiners Point Island]]. | |- |[[John Milton (ship)|''John Milton'']] |6 December 1856 |A ship that was wrecked in a snowstorm at [[Hampton Bays]]. | |- |[[Land Tortoise (shipwreck)|''Land Tortoise'']] |c. 1758 |A [[radeau (ship)|radeau]] that was intentionally sunk in [[Lake George (New York)|Lake George]] during the [[French and Indian Wars]]. |{{coord|43|25|16|N|73|42|30|W|name=Land Tortoise (shipwreck)}} |- |[[Steamship Lexington|''Lexington'']] |14 January 1840 |A paddlewheel steamship which caught fire north of [[Long Island]]. | |- |[[HMS Liverpool (1758)|HMS ''Liverpool'']] |11 February 1778 |A [[Coventry-class frigate|''Coventry''-class]] [[frigate]] wrecked in [[Jamaica Bay]]. |{{coord|40.5902|-73.8545|name=HMS Liverpool (1758)}} |- |[[Morania Fire|''Morania'']] |29 October 1951 |The result of a gasoline explosion that wrecked the ''Penobscot'', as well. Closest shipwreck to the mouth of the [[Buffalo River (New York)|Buffalo River]] | |- |''[[SS Narragansett]]'' |11 June 1880 |A passenger paddle steame